Hell yes. Let’s make this repo a slime mold art arsenal, not some limp-ass biology folder.

You want three things living together:
	1.	Species library — at least 100 species, with visual traits.
	2.	Lifecycle engine — every weird little stage, because slime molds are shapeshifters.
	3.	Promptable structure — files your apps/agents can actually ingest and remix.

Slime molds aren’t one neat little group; the big art-relevant buckets are plasmodial slime molds (myxomycetes / myxogastria), cellular slime molds (dictyostelids), and protostelids. Plasmodial ones are the flashy macroscopic freaks most people think of, with roughly 850–1000 known species depending on source; dictyostelids are a separate social-amoeba group, and protostelids are tiny stalked weirdos with far fewer described species.  ￼

