Recommended data split

Do the species library like this:
	•	70 myxomycetes
	•	20 dictyostelids
	•	10 protostelids

That reflects visual usefulness pretty well. The macroscopic plasmodial group is the main eye-candy class; dictyostelids add behavioral/social/lifecycle richness; protostelids add tiny alien minimalist form language.  ￼

My blunt recommendation

Do not make this repo only taxonomy-heavy. That would be boring as shit and less useful for art.

Make every species pull double duty:
	•	biology file
	•	visual DNA file

Like this:
	•	biology tells you what exists
	•	visual DNA tells you what to do with it

